>Original POST:
>
>Type 4- GE010 prefix= 79 2.l
>Bus- 76 Westy
>
>The problem is this:
>
>The engine idles fine, but when you rev it, there is a popping noise. It
>doesn't disappear when you pull any of the plugs. Lifters are adjusted at 2
>turns. Compression is good. Pulled a couple lifters and there is a bit of
>scoring on the surface, and they don't push in as others do- they are
>completely stiff. The PO said it threw a valve and replaced the heads,
>lifters, valves. Replaced with 914 head and VW OE valves and lifters.
>Could this cause popping?
>
>The bus is new to me. It ran fine for 2-3 weeks after I had it, and then one
>day it started popping like crazy. As a side note- I changed the exhaust from
>Monza style back to stock which is when this started. I pulled the exhaust
>back off, RTVd it, and no popping. Next day, popping. I don't know if it is a
>coincidence. There are no leaks that I can feel.
>
>UPDATE:
>
>The overwhelming response here was- exhaust leak.
>
>I called the mechanic this morning and told the whole story about the popping
>stopping after I re-installed the exhaust.. I told him I'd bring my old
>exhaust in to swap it and see if the noise stops, but he doesn't think that is
>the problem. He says the popping noise (not a metal/metal pop) is originating
>in the carb (Single Weber progressive).
>
>I am at a loss on this. What could it be?
